{
  "texts": [
    "More precisely, each one of the 41 regions classified as \"Default\" by the parcellation image was used as a binary mask to extract the time series from the functional image.",
    "For each subject (patient and control), the pair-wise Pearson correlation coefficient between time series was computed to obtain a functional connectivity matrix.",
    "The spatial overlap between DMNs and tumor masks was computed by summing all the voxels in the lesion mask belonging to one of these 41 regions.",
    "To normalize this score, we divided the resulting number by the number of voxels belonging to each one of the 41 regions labeled as \"Default\".",
    "Note that, with this definition, an overlap of 1 would mean the presence of a tumor the size of the entire DMN."
  ]
}